properties.headline: COVID-19 Border Controls - NSW-QUEENSLAND M1 Pacific Motorway approaching Queensland border
properties.otherAdvice:
The Queensland state government has imposed restrictions on cross-border movements as a result of the coronavirus pandemic.

  • Queensland, Heavy & Exempt vehicles should remain on the motorway
  • All other vehicles must exit onto the Gold Coast Hwy where there will be a police checkpoint

Exemptions include freight, emergency vehicles and emergency workers, people travelling to and from work, court orders including family court, compassionate grounds and medical treatment.

During peak travel periods, particularly weekday mornings, extensive delays may be experienced by motorists travelling into Queensland.

Visit qld.gov.au for more details.

Restrictions in effect include border road closures and police checks on vehicles on major highways.

Exemptions include freight, emergency vehicles and emergency workers, people travelling to and from work, court orders including family court, compassionate grounds and medical treatment.

  • Please call prior to travel as you will not have phone service at the gate/border.

properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS Bridge construction - MORORO TO CHATSWORTH ISLAND Pacific Hwy
properties.publicTransport:
Motorists are advised there will also be some changes to local bus stop pick up and drop off locations.  

  • The bus stop north of the old Mororo Bridge that was temporarily relocated to Woombah Woods Caravan Park will be reinstated to its original location.  
  • The school bus stop at Banana Road has been relocated to Woombah Woods Caravan Park bus stop on Iluka Road.

properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS Oversize vehicles - MOUNT VICTORIA Great Western Highway to River Lett Hill
properties.otherAdvice:
A series of 70m-long loads will travel down Victoria Pass and up River Lett Hill early on Monday to Saturday mornings through to September. For the safety of motorists, changed traffic conditions will be in place.

Eastbound traffic will be held at River Lett Hill and the bottom of Mount Victoria while the trucks use these sections of road and traffic will be stopped for 20-25 minutes between 4am and 5am.

Westbound motorists will experience delays while following the oversize vehicles which need to travel at low speed through this section.

properties.otherAdvice:
From 11am Sat 4 Jul until the operational launch of the Parramatta Light Rail:

Church Street will be closed to traffic in both directions between Victoria Road and Factory Street.

One southbound lane will be maintained on Church Street between Factory Street and Victoria Road for local access only.

There will be no through access at the following intersections along Church Street:

  • No access to Church Street from the eastern side of Albert Street.
  • No access to Church Street from the western side of Factory, Harold, Fennell and Ross Streets.

properties.headline: SPECIAL EVENT CLEARWAYS - Rail replacement bus operations - CHATSWOOD Railway St between Day St AND Help St
properties.otherAdvice:
Special event clearways will be in effect on the eastern side of Railway St between Day St and Help St from 2am Saturday 18 July until 2am Monday 20 July to facilitate rail replacement bus operations for Sydney Metro trackwork.

No-stopping zones will also be in place on the western side of Railway St between Help St and Brown St from 5pm Friday 17 July until 6am Monday 20 July.

Clearways are strict no-parking zones and apply even to local residents or RMS Mobility Scheme Permit holders. Check signs before parking as vehicles left in clearways will be towed and a fee applies.

Southbound motorists:
Alternative petrol stations - Shell Service Station at Wilton Rd, Wilton, located 5km north and the Shell Service Station, Old Hume Hwy, Balaclava, located 23km south.
Alternative rest area - south of the Bargo off ramp at Yanderra.

Northbound motorists:
Alternative petrol stations - BP Service Station at Remembrance Driveway, Bargo, located 7km south and Douglas Park Service Station at Camden Rd, Douglas Park, located 13km north.
Alternative rest area - Berrima rest area.

properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS M8 is now open - ST PETERS INTERCHANGE M8 westbound tunnel at Gardeners Rd and Euston Rd/Campbell Rd
properties.otherAdvice:
New traffic conditions are in place on Gardeners Rd and Campbell Rd/Euston Rd at the St Peters Interchange where westbound motorists can enter the new M8 tunnel.

Motorists should check signs on approach to the tunnel, and at the exit at Beverly Hills, to ensure they remain in the correct lane for their destination.

Dangerous goods/prohibited vehicles must not use the M8 and M5 East tunnels. Alternative routes are eastbound via King Georges Rd or Bexley Rd and westbound via Foreshore Rd.

Real-time travel and trip planning information may not be available until sufficient traffic volume data is collected.

For more information on the project visit westconnexm8.com.au.

properties.headline: COVID-19 Border Crossings - NSW-VICTORIA Newell Highway, Tocumwal near Victoria-NSW border
properties.otherAdvice:
The NSW state government has imposed restrictions on movements to/from Victoria as a result of the coronavirus pandemic.

Restrictions take effect from 12:01am Wednesday 8 July and include border road closures and police checks on vehicles on major highways.

Special conditions will be in place for freight operations and logistics as well as other critical services. Provisions will also be in place for residents of border regions, including Albury-Wodonga.

Transport for NSW is continuing to work closely with NSW Health, NSW Police and industry on a number of important issues including freight operations and logistics.

Visit health.nsw.gov.au for more details.

properties.headline: COVID-19 Border Controls - NSW-VICTORIA all crossing locations
properties.otherAdvice:
The NSW state government has imposed restrictions on cross-border movements as a result of the coronavirus pandemic. All non-essential travel should be avoided. Restrictions in place include border road closures and police checks on vehicles on major highways.  

Essential workers can continue their work. The freight network will be maintained and supply chains managed. If you are travelling from Victoria to NSW, you will need a COVID-19 NSW border declaration permit.  

Police and other resources will be at the following locations to help you cross the border from Victoria into NSW as quickly as possible.  

  • Wodonga Pl, South Albury
  • Hume Hwy, South Albury
  • Cobb Hwy, Moama
  • Newell Hwy, Tocumwal
  • Sturt Hwy, Buronga
  • Princes Hwy, Timbillica
